sentences: Julien Ranouil (French pronunciation: ​[ʒyljɛ̃ ʁanuj]; born 26 January 1981 in Bergerac), known by his stage name Pakito () or Karlux, is a French electronic dance music artist.
His cover of Trans-X's "Living on Video" reached number one on France's singles chart.
Later hits are "Moving on Stereo" and "Are U Ready".
So far his music style can be best determined as Eurodance.
His name is taken from 'Paquito el Chocolatero', a famous pasodoble dance from Alicante, in the Comunidad Valenciana region of Spain.
His album Video was released on November 8, 2006 in the United States.
2006: "Moving to the Beat" (Pakito vs. Black & White Brothers)
